g.text: 1. Ingest: High-resolution (0.05°) species distribution models (AquaMaps, Birds of the World, Critical Habitat).
2. Weight: Multiply cell presence (0-1) by Extinction Risk (0.2 - 1.0) based on IUCN/ESA status.
3. Group: Sum weighted scores by taxonomic component (e.g., all Birds, all Fish) + Primary Productivity.
4. Rescale: Normalize scores (0-100) based on min/max values within the specific Ecoregion.
5. Aggregate: Average the rescaled components within BOEM Planning Areas to visualize as Flower Plots.
